  "raw_text": "This document formalizes the five phase pipeline for predicting beneficial resolutions from raw conflict text using local zero dependency processing to generate emergent structures tension scores and actionable predictions for the Semantic Edge social science layer. The system processes conflict scenarios into a bottled API output with beneficial scores resolution paths and tension signals. Phase five is the API response. Phase four converts left right divergence into prediction scores where high tension flags intervention opportunities. Phase three computes tension via keyword similarity: shared keywords divided by total unique keywords equals similarity and one minus similarity equals tension score. Phase two builds emergent filesystem from clumps where co-occurrence exceeds two inferences. Phase one performs dual keyword extraction with left semantic nouns and right digital process terms. The master index aggregates inferences with tension scores and related clumps. Pure local co-occurrence with no external APIs.",
